1) LOOCV 

#Regsubset lm formulas
leaps <- regsubsets(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_ , nvmax=length(lmfit$coefficients)-1, method ="seqrep")
reg_ids <- summary(leaps)$which ## 
xvars <- dimnames(reg_ids)[[2]][-1]  ## column names (all covariates except intercept)
responsevar <- 'sqrt(MEDV)'  ## name of response


lst <- vector("list", length(lmfit$coefficients)-1)  ## set up an empty model list
h <- vector("list", length(lmfit$coefficients)-1)


for (i in 1:dim(reg_ids)[1]) {

     id <- reg_ids[i, ]
     # xvars   , regsubset         
     form <- reformulate(xvars[which(id[-1])], response=responsevar, id[1])
     lst[[i]] <- lm(form, data=boston_)
 
     MF <- model.frame(formula = form , data=boston_)
     MT <- attr(x = MF, which = "terms")
     mod1 <- lm(form, data=boston_)
     X <- model.matrix(object = MT, data = mod1$model)
     
     H=X%*%solve(t(X)%*%X, tol = 1e-20)%*%t(X) #singular torlerance 
     h[[i]]=diag(H)
}

## FIND LOOCV error
loocv_rss_stw <- mean((lst[[nrss]]$residuals /(1-h[[nrss]]))^2)
loocv_adjr2_stw <- mean((lst[[nadjr2]]$residuals /(1-h[[nadjr2]]))^2)
loocv_cp_stw <- mean((lst[[ncp]]$residuals /(1-h[[ncp]]))^2)
loocv_bic_stw <- mean((lst[[nbic]]$residuals /(1-h[[nbic]]))^2)

2) 10-fold Cross Validation

  • regsubset

  • for Cross Validation

  • regsubset prediction

  • Cross Validation MSE

  • object regsubset id Validation 

library(leaps)
#define predict regsubsets
predict.regsubsets = function(object, newdata, id, ...){
  form = as.formula(object$call[[2]])
  mat = model.matrix(form, newdata)
  coefi = coef(object, id=id)
  xvars = names(coefi)
  mat[,xvars]%*% coefi
}
  • 10-fold Cross Validation 
## 10-fold Cross validation
k=10
set.seed(1)
folds = sample(1:k, nrow(boston_), replace=T)
cv.errors = matrix(0,k,120)
for(j in 1:k){
  leaps_ <- regsubsets(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_[folds!=j,] , nvmax=length(lmfit$coefficients)-1, method ="seqrep")
    for(l in c(nrss,nadjr2, ncp, nbic)){
        pred = predict(leaps_,id=l,boston_[folds==j,])
        cv.errors[j,l] = mean((sqrt(boston_$MEDV[folds==j]) - pred )^2)
    }
}
cvs <- cv.errors[,c(nrss,nadjr2,ncp,nbic)]
colnames(cvs) <- c("RSS","ADJR2","CP","BIC")
cvs

1) RIDGE / LASSO

  • Ridge regression (L2 norm regularization)
#Ridge
library(glmnet)
library(tidyverse)

# Model Matrix for Training dataset
MF_t <- model.frame(formula = sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_)
MT_t <- attr(x = MF_t, which = "terms")
mod1_t <- lm(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2, data=boston_)
X <- model.matrix(object = MT_t, data = mod1_t$model)

# Model Matrix for Test dataset
MF_e <- model.frame(formula = sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_test)
MT_e <- attr(x = MF_e, which = "terms")
mod1_e <- lm(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2, data=boston_test)
X_e <- model.matrix(object = MT_e, data = mod1_e$model)

x=X[,-1]
x_test=X_e[,-1]
y=sqrt(boston_$MEDV)
y_test=sqrt(boston_test$MEDV)

lambdas = 10^seq(3, -3, by = -.1)
cv.out=cv.glmnet(x, y, alpha=0, nfolds=10, lambda=lambdas) 
plot(cv.out)

lambda_opt=cv.out$lambda.min 
ridge_mod = glmnet(x,y,alpha=0,lambda = lambda_opt)


ridge_pred =  predict(ridge_mod,s=lambda_opt,newx= x_test)
coef_ridge = predict(ridge_mod,type="coefficients",s=lambda_opt )
mse_ridge = mean((ridge_pred^2 - y_test^2)^2) # Calculate test MSE
#coef_ridge
cat("test MSE Ridge:" ,mse_ridge)
## test MSE Ridge: 12.33892
  • LASSO regression (L1 norm regularization)
#LASSO
library(glmnet)
library(tidyverse)

# Model Matrix for Training dataset
MF_t <- model.frame(formula = sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_)
MT_t <- attr(x = MF_t, which = "terms")
mod1_t <- lm(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2, data=boston_)
X <- model.matrix(object = MT_t, data = mod1_t$model)

# Model Matrix for Test dataset
MF_e <- model.frame(formula = sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2 , data=boston_test)
MT_e <- attr(x = MF_e, which = "terms")
mod1_e <- lm(sqrt(MEDV)~(.+I(LSTAT^2) + I(RM^2))^2, data=boston_test)
X_e <- model.matrix(object = MT_e, data = mod1_e$model)

x=X[,-1]
x_test=X_e[,-1]
y=sqrt(boston_$MEDV)
y_test=sqrt(boston_test$MEDV)

lambdas = 10^seq(3, -3, by = -.1)
cv.out=cv.glmnet(x, y, alpha=1, nfolds=10, lambda=lambdas)
plot(cv.out)

lambda_opt=cv.out$lambda.min 
lasso_mod = glmnet(x,y,alpha=1,lambda = lambda_opt)


lasso_pred =  predict(lasso_mod,s=lambda_opt,newx= x_test)
coef_lasso = predict(lasso_mod,type="coefficients",s=lambda_opt )
mse_lasso = mean((lasso_pred^2 - y_test^2)^2) # Calculate test MSE
cat("test MSE LASSO:" ,mse_lasso)
## test MSE LASSO: 13.31907
